The ‘uncus' is an iron cramp which, fastened by molten lead, was used to join blocks of stone, such as the joints ofa column, Vitr. 2. S. The implements which Necessitas carries are all emblems of the fixity of her sentence. The point is not that they are implements of building, but that they are the implements which make a building indissoluble.
